  <notes>
Completed 2026-05-19 by sub-agent (main-session-coordinated parallel wave). Build-only verification, no deploys (per user instruction — manual MSAL regression test is per-deploy, not per-PCF).

## Scope discovery (correction vs POML prompt)

Grep across src/client/pcf/* showed SIX active PCFs depend on @spaarke/auth (not three as POML suggested):
- UniversalDatasetGrid (was in POML)
- SpeDocumentViewer (was in POML)
- SemanticSearchControl (NEW — found via grep)
- RelatedDocumentCount (NEW — found via grep)
- EmailProcessingMonitor (NEW — found via grep)
- DocumentRelationshipViewer (NEW — found via grep)

UniversalQuickCreate (in POML) does NOT depend on @spaarke/auth — uses raw @azure/msal-browser. Out of scope for this task; would need full Phase B migration to enter v2.

## v2 cleanliness audit (per-PCF source review)

| PCF | authInit.ts | Removed v1 symbols? | Bearer ${...} literals? | accessToken/token: string props? |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| UniversalDatasetGrid | Clean (initAuth + getAuthProvider) | None | Services use `Bearer ${token}` w/ getAccessToken() — uses @spaarke/auth provider, not removed symbols | Pre-existing types/auth.ts file with `AuthToken.accessToken: string` (legacy MSAL adapter type, not in current data flow) |
| SpeDocumentViewer | Clean (initAuth) | None | BffClient uses authenticatedFetch (clean) | Pre-existing dead-code: hooks/useDocumentPreview.ts and useCheckoutFlow.ts still accept `accessToken: string` param (marked DEPRECATED, no longer used by host). AuthService.ts marked @deprecated. Dead-code cleanup recommended in future pass. |
| SemanticSearchControl | Clean (initAuth) | None | Uses @spaarke/auth | Clean |
| RelatedDocumentCount | Clean (initAuth + resolveTenantFromXrm comments) | None | Uses @spaarke/auth | Clean |
| EmailProcessingMonitor | Clean (initAuth) | None | Uses @spaarke/auth | Clean |
| DocumentRelationshipViewer | Has `authority: https://login.microsoftonline.com/${tenantId}` (other consumers comment this out per MSAL popup regression fix from 2026-05-13) | None | Uses @spaarke/auth | types/auth.ts has legacy `accessToken: string` type (not in active data flow) |

**No source-code migration required.** All 6 PCFs were already on the v2 contract (function-based, no v1 strategy symbols). Residual pre-existing dead code (deprecated AuthService.ts, accessToken prop fields) is NOT auth-flow-active and is out of task 028 scope.

## Build infrastructure fixes (necessary to run build:prod cleanly)

Applied 3 minimal package.json fixes that this task surfaced:
1. **EmailProcessingMonitor/package.json**: added `"build:prod": "pcf-scripts build --buildMode production"` (was missing — would have shipped dev-mode bundle, per AP-1 failure mode)
2. **DocumentRelationshipViewer/package.json**: same fix (was missing build:prod)
3. **UniversalDatasetGrid/package.json**: added `eslint: ^8.57.1` to devDependencies (pcf-scripts peer-dep was unsatisfied; npm install failed without --legacy-peer-deps AND `Cannot find module 'eslint'` at build time; all other 5 PCFs declare eslint directly)

These are infrastructure-level fixes, not auth changes.

Also: `@spaarke/ui-components/dist/` did not exist when starting; built with selective tsc (per pcf-deploy SKILL.md Step 1.5) using `--strict false` because of pre-existing TypeScript errors in SprkChat/*.tsx (concurrent task 023 territory — will resolve when 023 ships). All 1196 dist files emitted; all PCF-required modules (themeStorage, logger, MiniGraph, RelationshipCountCard, FindSimilarDialog, RecordCardShell, AiSummaryPopover, SendEmailDialog, DocumentEmailWizard, types/*) verified present.

